metadata_comment: Allows instances to call AWS Systems Manager (SSM) APIs, useful for managing instances.
Provides full access to Amazon Elastic Container Registry (ECR) to manage Docker container repositories.
Provides full access to manage Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) resources, including creating subnets, route tables, and managing IP addressing.
Provides full access to Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) services, including the ability to create, modify, and delete instances.
Provides access to view and manage AWS support resources
Provides access to manage AWS Secrets Manager secrets
Provides full access to manage IAM users, groups, and roles
Provides access to view and manage billing and cost management
Provides full access to manage database services and resources
Provides read-only access to all AWS services and resources
Provides full access to manage AWS systems and infrastructure
Provides full access to AWS services and resources
Provides access to manage and analyze data within AWS services
Provides read-only access to security-related information
Provides full access to manage network resources and configurations
Provides access to manage AWS Support Center and Support API
Provides full access to AWS services except for management of users and groups
Provides full access to manage AWS service quotas
Provides full access to manage AWS Resource Access Manager
